# API Controllers

## BaseController pattern

```csharp
// ✅ GOOD — thin entity controller
public class TaskController(AppDbContext context) : BaseController<TaskItem>(context)
{
    // Custom endpoints only; CRUD inherited
}
```

`BaseController<T>` provides `GET`, `GET/{id}`, `POST`, `PUT/{id}`, `DELETE/{id}` with `[Authorize]`.

## Custom endpoints

```csharp
[HttpGet("completed")]
public async Task<ActionResult<IEnumerable<TaskItem>>> GetCompleted()
{
    return await _dbSet.Where(t => t.IsCompleted).ToListAsync();
}
```

## Routes

`[Route("api/[controller]")]` → `/api/task` (controller name minus `Controller` suffix).

## Validation

Override `Post`/`Put` for domain rules; return `BadRequest()` with clear messages.

```csharp
// ❌ BAD — new controller without [Authorize] on class
[ApiController]
public class TaskController : ControllerBase { ... }

// ✅ GOOD — inherit BaseController (includes [Authorize])
public class TaskController(AppDbContext context) : BaseController<TaskItem>(context);
```

## Auth controller

`AuthController` is separate — does not inherit `BaseController`; uses `[AllowAnonymous]` on login/register.
